    "where W is a rank one local system on ∂ with monodromy (-1) s.",
    "• The fission local system V is determined as follows: For any Stokes path γ î→ ĵ in the fission surface Σ(Θ), the corresponding parallel transport ρ î→ ĵ is obtained, up to a sign (which is explicitly determined), by pulling back the endpoints î, ĵ to the initial fission surface Σ(Θ) using the inverse of the Legendre transform and taking the parallel transport in the fission local system V along the (natural) path from ℓ -1 (î) to ℓ -1 (ĵ), i.e.",
    "Let us note that one has to carefully keep track of the signs in the formal local system here in order to correctly determine V from the parallel transports along the Stokes paths.",
    "In particular, the sign (-1) s comes by gluing the graded pieces of the formal local system from several intervals and introducing multiple signs in this gluing process, which is made precise in Section 5.",
    "In particular, this allows us to compute the Stokes matrices of (E, ∇) as a function of the Stokes matrices of (E, ∇)."
